      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The argument that these regulations are a political agenda to favor big corporations over small family businesses is a common critique, but it is often based on a misunderstanding of how market competition actually works. While the transition costs are real, the long-term economic benefit comes from creating a level playing field where all companies must operate within the same environmental standards, preventing large firms from gaining an unfair advantage by ignoring pollution controls. Ultimately, this policy aims to ensure the industry's survival by eliminating practices that are unsustainable in the long run, regardless of whether the initial impact feels harsh on individual owners.",
